<subSubSection id="766FB6DD04C81230EB46BC778F7F01C1" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="123" pageId="1" pageNumber="122" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="11FE8CB25B45882BB5594D33F1ED7A3C" pageId="1" pageNumber="122">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="604EE7BA67B73A296E1B18B3AF78AADA" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="123" pageId="1" pageNumber="122">
This species was first described by Breuning in 
<bibRefCitation id="EA659C11DA40C31CA215C221C3CBAC2E" author="Breuning, S" journalOrPublisher="Miscellanea Entomologica" pageId="9" pageNumber="130" pagination="141 - 149" title="Nouveaux Cerambycides palearctiques (4 e note)." volume="43" year="1947">1947</bibRefCitation>
based on a specimen from Sichuan Province, China but it was downgraded to a variety of 
<taxonomicName id="70E2734DCC4BA830AAAACF12074C365C" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oberea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oberea atropunctata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atropunctata">
<pageBreakToken id="F624767C8BE10F2C0A48B3981BC123AF" pageId="2" pageNumber="123" start="start">Oberea</pageBreakToken>
atropunctata
</taxonomicName>
Pic, 1916 in his revisionary work (
<bibRefCitation id="8B5627A49B108B1F872523D8E7132652" author="Breuning, S" journalOrPublisher="Frustula Entomologica" pageId="9" pageNumber="130" pagination="1 - 59" title="Revision systematique des especes du genre Oberea Mulsant de globe (ColeopteraCerambycidae) (1 re Partie)." volume="3" year="1960">1960</bibRefCitation>
- 
<bibRefCitation id="244E9BD3591B11B64F62749D5BB0B122" author="Breuning, S" journalOrPublisher="Frustula Entomologica" pageId="9" pageNumber="130" pagination="141 - 232" title="Revision systematique des especes du genre Oberea Mulsant de globe (ColeopteraCerambycidae) (3 me Partie)." volume="5" year="1962">1962</bibRefCitation>
). A careful examination and comparison of the types of 
<taxonomicName id="AE30A8D307741CFBFCBC266B85FC82F5" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oberea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oberea flavescens" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavescens">Oberea flavescens</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CA0FAF752789AB2FB545D2ECCF56B7C5" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oberea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oberea atropunctata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atropunctata">Oberea atropunctata</taxonomicName>
(Figs 4-5) show that they are different species. 
<taxonomicName id="FF0A7B3EB8AEBEA33C5CE68F1AADD4BD" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oberea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oberea flavescens" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavescens">Oberea flavescens</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="D810AACD79677A5D626E1719117289B3" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oberea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oberea atropunctata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atropunctata">Oberea atropunctata</taxonomicName>
in having longer elytra and shorter antennae. They can be distinguished by having differently shaped male genitalia, the long pair of rods being 3.5 times as long as the short pair (1.5 times as long as in 
<taxonomicName id="BE7BEBFF898B4983C6DE5C3D292818FF" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oberea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oberea atropunctata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atropunctata">Oberea atropunctata</taxonomicName>
) and the short pair consisting of two simple short rods.
</paragraph>
<caption id="01A4E9727032D7CC034A4B7199E48622" pageId="2" pageNumber="123">
<paragraph id="65D62400F1FCC1E494E0B041A6973833" pageId="2" pageNumber="123">
Figure 4. Habitus of 
<taxonomicName id="C057905387C1B164D1DF5D87F9DD87D7" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oberea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oberea atropunctata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atropunctata">Oberea atropunctata</taxonomicName>
Pic, 1916, 
<normalizedToken id="F1C75256DBE873DE4B1789ED4B9C1997" originalValue="aâ€“c">a-c</normalizedToken>
holotype, female, from Yunnan a dorsal view b lateral view c label (not to scale) 
<normalizedToken id="0F74B7D1F1AF32BA9F22C8E870431AA8" originalValue="dâ€“e">d-e</normalizedToken>
male, from Yunnan d dorsal view, e lateral view. Scale bar 5.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
